				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Shielding % Mods...weaker than advertised, or broken?<a name="47258"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 21 04 2:00 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hopefully someone with more shielding than I have has tested this.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I finnally got my first shielding item, Greaves of Furious Might, from PoTime --- 4% Shielding.
<br />

<br />
Now, the way I'd understood it previously, Shielding % was a direct reduction from a mobs attack.  Aka, if a mob hit for 100, it would only hit for 96.  To test, if a mobs max hit was 100, it's max hit should be reduced to 96.  Sitting Down causes a mob to hit for max of course.
<br />

<br />
But this doesn't seem to be the case.
<br />

<br />
I won't say I've done alot of testing with this, but then the effect is pretty obvious right off the bat.
<br />

<br />
Light Blue mob in Freeport --- Legs on, 112 Max hit, Legs off, 112 Max hit.
<br />

<br />
Dark Blue Guard in Freeport, Legs - 173 Max, No Legs 175 Max.
<br />

<br />
Dark Blue mob in PoV -- Legs - 431, No Legs 434 max hit.
<br />

<br />
Now, according to the numbers, not only does the % seem to vary, but it's far lower than 4%.  In the first instance it was 0%, the Second, about 1%, and the 3rd roughly .50%.
<br />

<br />
Anyone know what the deal is here?  .50 to 1% is pretty disapointingly low.
<br />

<br />

<br />
In other news, I got a Songblade of the Eternal Tonight so pretty happy regardless<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.</span></td>
