				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Shielding % Mods...weaker than advertised, or broken?<a name="47335"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 21 04 12:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Go to the steel warrior board for best information on shielding. The damage you take from a mobs melee is based on a damage bonus and a damage interval. Shielding only works against one of them (just like defensive). </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Close;
<br />

<br />
Damage taken = Damage base + [(RNG(1,20) * DI) * .95]
<br />
for warriors
<br />

<br />
and 
<br />
Damage taken = Damage base + (RNG(1,20) * DI)
<br />

<br />
Shielding lowers the DB number. You will really start to notice shielding once you hit 10+. I am sitting at shielding 18 and I get hit for a lot less on average now.
<br />

<br />
Grats on your songblade.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
